# Privacy Policy - Everything 2x

**Last updated:** 6 April 2026

## Overview

Everything 2x is a Chrome extension that automatically plays videos at 2x speed while detecting music videos and keeping them at normal speed. This privacy policy explains how the extension handles user data.

## Data Collection

Everything 2x does **not** collect, store, transmit, or share any user data. Specifically, the extension does not collect:

- Personal information (name, email, address, or any identifiers)
- Browsing history or web activity
- Authentication or financial information
- Location data
- Website content
- Usage analytics or telemetry

## How the Extension Works

The extension reads page metadata (title, structured data, YouTube category) locally in your browser to determine whether a video is music content. This analysis happens entirely on your device. No page content or metadata is sent to any server.

## Data Storage

The extension stores per-tab speed override preferences in memory only. These reset when the tab is closed. No data is written to disk or synced externally.

## Third Parties

No user data is sold, transferred, or disclosed to any third party.

## Permissions

- **tabs:** Used to send speed control messages between the popup and the active tab.
- **host_permissions (<all_urls>):** Required to inject the content script that controls video playback speed on any webpage.

These permissions are not used to read, collect, or transmit any page content or user data.

